title: Zoo AC-6 — trait-declared state survives undo and save/restore
story: friendly-zoo
description: ADR-210 AC-6, Phase C P5 (additive to the Phase B gate; P4
  status note 3): feedable's `states, reversible: hungry, content` is a
  TRAIT-declared set — Phase B's AC-6 transcripts covered occurrence
  counters and entity-declared states only. Feeding flips the goats
  hungry → content with no author-written persistence code: undo must roll
  the transition back so feeding succeeds again, and the content refusal
  must survive save/restore (a reset-to-initial would feed successfully).

---

# Into the Petting Zoo; the goats start hungry
> south
[OK: contains "Main Path"]

> east
[OK: contains "Petting Zoo"]

> take feed
[OK: contains "Taken"]

# hungry → content
> feed goats
[OK: contains "devour the corn and pellets"]

# Undo rolls the trait-state transition back along with the turn
> undo
[EVENT: true, type="platform.undo_completed"]

# Hungry again: feeding succeeds a second time
> feed goats
[OK: contains "devour the corn and pellets"]

$save ac6-goats-content

# Content: the refusal proves the state
> feed goats
[OK: contains "already fed them"]

$restore ac6-goats-content

# Still content after restore — trait state rides the save with no author
# persistence code
> feed goats
[OK: contains "already fed them"]
